HEADWORD: Libethenite
<hw>Li*beth"en*ite</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧*b⟦ecr⟧th"⟦ecr⟧n*⟦imac⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <ets>Libethen</ets>, in Hungary, where it was
first found.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of an olive-green
color, commonly in orthorhombic crystals. It is a hydrous phosphate of
copper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>libidinal</ent>⟦br⟧
